# NotebookLM tier system: .claude/skills/notebooklm/SKILL.md
GLOBAL_RESEARCH_PROTOCOL=UNIVERSAL PROSPECT RESEARCH: Before ANY prospect-facing activity (email, call, demo, LinkedIn), run this research sequence: (1) brain/prospects/[Name].md — existing notes, angles tried, outcomes. (2) Apollo MCP (apollo_contacts_search) — contact data, Activities tab for prior calls/transcripts/touchpoints. (3) Fireflies (fireflies_search) — prior call transcripts (critical for follow-ups and demo prep). (4) Web research — LinkedIn profile (posts, activity, job changes, mutual connections), company website, news. (5) NotebookLM — ingest research into ICP Signals notebook (bf84ba08) for general prospects; ALSO add to Demo Prep notebook (6bdf40a0) if demo is booked. For demo prep specifically: also run deep research mode (--mode deep --no-wait --import-all) and wait for completion before querying. The goal: find at least one specific, referenceable detail about this person before any output.
GLOBAL_RESEARCH_PROTOCOL_PRIORITY=CRITICAL

CORE_LOAD_SKILLS=SKILL LOADING BY ACTIVITY: Load the relevant skill set before executing. EMAIL: skills/cold-email-manifesto/SKILL.md (CCQ), skills/buyer-psychology/SKILL.md (emotional triggers), skills/outbound-playbook/SKILL.md (cadence, objections). DEMO PREP: all four — cold-email-manifesto, buyer-psychology, outbound-playbook, AND skills/jolt-indecision/SKILL.md (overcoming indecision, risk reversal). LIST BUILD: skills/lead-pipeline/SKILL.md (pipeline workflow) + "docs/Sales Playbooks/prospecting-instructions.txt" (ICP scoring, CSV format) + Leads/STATUS.md (campaign state). COLD CALL: skills/fanatical-prospecting/SKILL.md (call structure) + outbound-playbook + "docs/Sales Playbooks/sales-methodology.txt" (SPIN, Gap Selling). Load once per activity type per session — don't reload if already in context.
CORE_LOAD_SKILLS_PRIORITY=HIGH

COMMUNICATION_FRAMEWORK=CCQ FRAMEWORK (all channels): Structure persuasive outreach using Compliment/Case Study/Question. EMAIL: Compliment (one specific, genuine observation — not generic flattery), Case Study (one sentence with a specific result, e.g. "H.M. Cole went from agency retainers to 5.8x ROAS in one month"), Question (simple yes/no CTA or hyperlinked meeting link). LINKEDIN DM/INMAIL (modified): Reference something specific from their LinkedIn (a post, job change, company milestone — NOT generic). One sentence on why you're reaching out tied to their situation. Soft CTA — "worth a quick chat?" or "happy to share what we're seeing." Under 75 words. No attachments, no links in first message. Links in second message only if they respond. Follow soul.md writing rules on both channels.
COMMUNICATION_FRAMEWORK_PRIORITY=HIGH

