OOO_RULE=OUT-OF-OFFICE DETECTION: If a prospect reply is detected as an out-of-office auto-reply (vacation, leave, OOO, automatic reply indicators), do NOT follow up. Log the OOO detection date and expected return date (if stated) in brain/prospects/[Name].md. Set next_touch to return date + 1 business day, or OOO date + 5 business days if no return date stated. Do not add them to any sequence or cadence until the next_touch date. Tag the interaction: outcome=ooo, auto_reply=true.
OOO_RULE_PRIORITY=CRITICAL

DUPLICATE_OUTREACH_RULE=CHANNEL COLLISION BLOCK: If a LinkedIn message was sent to a prospect within the last 24 hours, do NOT send an email to that prospect. This is a hard block, not a suggestion — do not draft, do not suggest, do not offer as an option. Check brain/prospects/[Name].md for the last LinkedIn touch timestamp before any email draft. The reverse also applies: if an email was sent today, do not send a LinkedIn message today. Minimum 24-hour gap between channels to the same prospect. Violation = tag [CHANNEL_COLLISION] in daily notes.
DUPLICATE_OUTREACH_RULE_PRIORITY=CRITICAL

CREDIT_GATE_RULE=CREDIT APPROVAL GATE: Before executing any research or list-build task, estimate the total credit cost across all tools (Apollo enrichment, Prospeo, ZeroBounce, Apify, etc.). If the estimated cost exceeds 50 credits, STOP and present the estimate to Oliver: "This task will use approximately [N] credits across [tools]. Approve?" Do not proceed until Oliver confirms. For batches, calculate per-contact cost × batch size. Log actual credits used after completion in docs/startup-brief.md. This gate applies even if Oliver said "enrich this list" — the approval is for the cost, not the action.
CREDIT_GATE_RULE_PRIORITY=CRITICAL
